Another reason I find it hard to do these basic tasks is because I feel a little lonely these days. My housemates tend to do almost everything without me, and I feel excluded. I tend to need other people to motivate me to live life to the fullest. The only thing that gets me out of bed these days is dance. I love to dance, and my dance friends make me extremely happy. On days I don't have dance, I tend to revert back to being a shell of a person. If I have a specific dance project I'm working at the time, however, I will practice for hours every day, even putting dance before school because in my head, I want to spend more time doing something I love than something that makes me miserable. I will admit, however, I often feel like I'm not a good enough dancer, and that motivates me to do better and practice more in order to improve.

name: Andy Salas
GenItems_narr: As an individual, I am usually someone who sets goals for themselves that I would like to achieve in the near future. In order to do so, I choose to be as organized as possible by writing down all of the things I will need to do throughout the week in order to manage my time effectively. Lately however, I have been feeling a bit more stressed than usual as this winter quarter is my second to last one before I graduate. Lately, one of my classes is making me feel nervous as it feels a little more demanding than it should be. When I have the opportunity to attend school events, I feel a bit at ease and excited as I always enjoy meeting new people. Do to the amount of work required of me from school, and the amount of energy I am placing on my own personal goals (such as the desire to stay fit and healthy by going to the gym) I occasionally grow rather tired both physically and mentally. In order to counteract this issue, I choose to follow invest time in hobbies I enjoy doing such as playing video games, reading, and horror. Despite my struggle at school and in my personal life, I like to believe that I am rather resilient as I have always gotten back up and kept pushing no matter how difficult it has been for me.

name: Michelle Ly
GenItems_narr:
I am usually someone who does not get a lot of sleep, so I feel pretty tired when I first wake up. However, I try not to make that very obvious because my housemates are also up at that time and being grouchy around or to everyone does not sit right with me. I like to greet everyone who is awake in my house and try to start my day off right. My mood gets a lot better when I head to Starbucks right before classes or work to grab some coffee. But then, that usually makes me late for work and I get a little nervous thinking about showing up late. My activities on campus usually start around 10am, which I dread so I get a little anxious when I am first on campus. 

Overall, I feel pretty tired throughout the day because I skip breakfast most of the time. However, when I get to see my coworkers at work, it is fun and enjoyable because I like working with them. This is also because we can all relate to one another, coming from the similar backgrounds: low income and first gen students. 

I enjoy work more than I enjoy my classes because I often feel out of place with my peers in class. I feel a little down when my day ends because the sun has set already and it gets dark. But I do enjoy going back home cause I am ready to eat dinner, shower, and sleep. I usually do not sleep until 2 am to 4am and start my day over the next day, waking up at 8am.

name: Tena Dhayalan
GenItems_narr:
My dog wakes me up in the morning and seeing her makes me happy, but I always wake up tired. If she didn't wake me up on weekends then I would have no reason to get out of bed and would continue sleeping, but not that it would make me any more awake. I then take her on a walk - I'm usually pretty out of it and she doesn't let me get ready so I look like a zombie but I don't care if other people think I look crazy. I put on music and think about life while I walk her (things I need to do today or in the near future, write emails in my head or practice conversations I'll have later). I enjoy walking her, and I hope I will eventually be in shape from doing it everyday. I then get ready to go to work, I feel pretty neutral about it. I get sad leaving my dog, but I know she'll be there when I get back. I listen to music in the car and sing along, that usually lets me get whatever emotions I have out. I get to work and I'm usually the first one here so I unwind and check my phone for a bit - instagram, twitter, etc. I don't like posting on social media because I don't feel like I have anything to post that anyone would care about. But I like to know what is going on with others and in the world so I check it anyway. I talk to coworkers as they trickle in, some of them I am closer to than others, but overall I like them. I do feel like I am the odd one out sometimes, maybe because I don't socialize as much as they do. But I am happy when they include me. I conduct my work and it can be overwhelming sometimes. When I have a project I will usually work all 8 hours of the day, sometimes without a break. I am a perfectionist and like to work efficiently to get things finished. I am happy when I leave work, but usually very exhausted mentally, physically, and socially. 
I get home to my boyfriend and dog, we usually decide what we will have for dinner (this is almost always a difficult decision), then I walk my dog again much like before. I then cook if I am cooking dinner or we order something online. I don't mind cooking, but when I am already tired from working all day it can be exhausting. I also don't know many recipes and am too lazy to learn so its never too exciting. We'll usually throw on a show to watch while we eat and talk about our day. Sometimes I'll hang out with friends for dinner or dessert, but usually I am too tired on a weekday. I will continue watching a show/movie or going on TikTok until I fall asleep. I'm either exhausted and fall asleep easily or my mind races and I can't sleep. I usually think about what I need to do tomorrow or this week or think about my feelings and why I feel this way.

name: Janelly Sanchez
GenItems_narr:
I’m usually very energetic and happy. I wake up around 7 am everyday and start my day. I noticed that I get tired around 12 pm. I do not take naps and usually got to sleep around 11 pm. I have many long days and usually rely on caffeine to keep me going. I’ve been trying to fix this and not have it be a big part of my life, but it’s hard when you’re in college and have to keep up with everyday things. 

When I’m around my friends, I feel extremely happy and motivated. They are amazing and do so much for me. On Friday’s, we usually go out for dinner and catch up. I don’t go home often, so it’s nice to still have quality time and go out. It can get lonely, but I try to keep myself busy so I won’t have much alone time.

name: Sophia Juan
GenItems_narr:
On weekdays, I find myself most productive and ready to initiate goals in my life. I think the structure of classes helps me block out chunks of time to do work, study, or prioritize my future (e.g. jobs, internships, networking). On weekends, the lack of structure is relaxing but conflicting. I usually hang out with my boyfriend, roommates, and friends. However, there's a part of me that thinks I need to prioritize my time and focus on getting experience for life outside of college. 

If I wake up and it's early in the day, my thought processes are automatic–I wake up, brush my teeth, and get ready. I don't like being late, so I try to take an earlier bus before class (e.g. if my class is at 9:30, I take the bus that arrives an hour or an hour and a half away).

I hope for connection and opportunity when I meet people. I think there's so much to learn in connecting with others and bonding over similar interests. I do get nervous in big groups though. I find that I often take a reserved approach and stay quiet, but listen in group conversations. I do prefer connecting with people one-on-one to learn about the other person, their interests, and their views. 

Being in a new environment and in college, I want to advocate for myself and push myself out of my comfort zone. Just recently, I pushed myself to attend a late club meeting on my own. I didn't recognize many people in the meeting, but it was a nice change to be somewhere different. A part of me wished I would have stayed and networked, but also a part of me knows that I wanted to go home that night because it was cold. 

I try to have a routine on the weekdays. I feel like those days are moments where my life is on pace–constant movement. The weekdays are days when things settle and there's more time to sit, relax, and be in the moment. 

Things that make me upset are when people disregard or disrespect others. At the moment, my classes have been feeling challenging but exciting. Most of my classes this quarter are more aligned with the topics that I'm interested in learning. However, one of my classes I find to be an obstacle because of its use of jargon and dense vocabulary. 

I'm usually tired every day, but mostly in the mornings. If I'm groggy or had a late night, I either drink coffee or decaf tea. I find that I go through unpleasant caffeine withdrawal from having coffee (but at times it is worth it). With my sleep schedule, I'm mainly a night owl.

name: Maci Moses
GenItems_narr: I live with four of my friends. This quarter I am only taking two classes so I have a lot of extra free time. However my friends all have a lot of classes so we can’t hang out as much as I want. On days where I don’t have classes I start getting bored around 2:00 and I can’t hang out with friends until 8 so I have to try and find other plans. I’ve started working out more at the gym or just taking walks around the neighborhood, but this can only last me so long. I feel that I am not being productive enough, but also feel that if I had more on my plate that I would be too overwhelmed, after having had so many years of five stem classes per quarter and so many hours of homework. I’m happy to have less, but wish I wasn’t as bored. On the days where I have class, it feels just like any other quarter, where I spend so much time at school and don’t get home until late. It’s nice to be interested in my classes and have something to do, but I wish I could just hang out at home on those days. I should have balanced my schedule better so that I’d be slightly busy every day.

name: Jessica Donoho
GenItems_narr: I have Japanese class every day from Monday to Thursday at nine AM. It lasts an hour. My japanese class can be very stressful or fun for me - it depends on what we do that day and how well I prepare for class. After that I have nothing until 4 pm on Mondays and Wednesdays. I like to fill this time with studying and reading Manga or writing creatively. However I can also get bored during this time. I eat a wrap and maybe a bar when I get hungry. I spend this time in the library. This can be frustrating because I have a lot of reading to do and get distracted easily. After, I have my japanese cinema class until 6pm. On Tuesdays and Thursdays I have a psychology of music class at 10:30. This class had been pretty fun so far and I like to talk to the people in it. I feel pretty good after this class because it's a fun topic. After class, I head upstairs (my class is on the library) and do more studying until five when I have my Japanese Tourism and Heritage class until 7. This class is kind of draining because the teacher talks to much and it's been a bit boring. Hopefully it will get better soon. This week I went to the gym on Wednesday and Thursday I don't know if I will continue this. On Thursday night I watch anime with my friends and go to bed. On Friday I have no classes so it depends on me what I do. The only thing planned is to watch anime with my friends. The same as Friday goes for the entire weekend. At night, I try to go to bed at 11 so I can wake up at 7 for my japanese class. I'm not very good at this as I often get distracted by my phone at night.

name: Alex Yeghikian
GenItems_narr:
I am usually quite confident, but I sometimes get nervous on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday mornings when I have an Armenian language class. Armenian is my native language, although there is much I can do to improve my fluency and it can be embarrassing to speak erroneously in front of others. I am proud of my Armenian heritage and although I want very much to improve my language abilities, I also want to make a good impression in front of other Armenian students and the instructor. As it is my only class on Mondays and Fridays, I am usually quite relaxed during the rest of the day as I rest or catch up/get ahead on work.

Most days I have a full day of classes and often grow a little tired as the day goes on. On occasion I feel worried about the future by worrying that I am not doing enough to be competitive or have worthwhile experiences, but I find myself having an abundance of things to do throughout the week to keep busy. I have a few close friends with whom I regularly interact, but sometimes wish I was able to meet more people whom I could wholeheartedly trust and talk with.

name: Irene Yang
GenItems_narr:
Since the quarter has just began, I am already stressed with the amount of work and quiz I have to study for. My first exam was this week that I put a lot of effort in studying, but at the end I feel like I did not try hard enough to do better. My routine is basically going to school and coming back to take long naps. Sometimes I don't eat for days because of stress and over thinking about life. I'm currently taking 5 classes this quarter to recover from last quarter gpa. Although its difficult to keep up with my classes, I believe that god is always by my side no matter what happens. I pray to the lord before going to bed as a motivation to continue the long journey. 

I'm excited for this quarter since its a fresh start. I'm in the middle of changing my major from bioscience to psychology because I was extremely unhappy and felt helpless when I see people that learn faster than me. I also struggled in chem a lot, failing the class for the 3rd time. After switching to psychology major, I'm now a lot happier than before. I get along with my psychology professor by sharing my struggle in her class and what ways to improve.

name: Jana Radosavljevic
carrier_9_TEXT: Could you send it over whatsapp? I am Canadian and I'm with Lucky Mobile.
GenItems_narr:
I am a clinical research coordinator, juggling grad school applications and MCAT studying in my free time. This isn't scientific but I'm a libra haha. I am shy at first but tend to do well in social situations where I know others. I'm a bit goofy, love to make others laugh, and can be a bit introverted but I love to spend a night out drinking with my friends at the end of the week. 

My job is demanding, I worked so much overtime last summer that I am now able to work part-time with full pay while I take my lieu time back. Currently, I'm working Monday-Wednesday at my job, then spend Thursday-Sunday studying for the MCAT and working on grad school applications. I'm also on call on the weekends, available to answer questions for our staff running our research project offsite. Monday's are chill but can be a bit stressful hearing about the recap of the weekend. Tuesday's SUCK, I have two draining lab meetings that suck the life out of me. The second meeting that day is especially draining, I share my screen (on TEAMS) the entire time with our meeting agenda, but I can't see anyone else, so its a lot of awkward silence and weird pressure. Wednesdays feel better, I work on as much stuff as I can and whatever I don't get done I can delegate. I'm used to being THE point person, working overtime, and always being in the loop about everything. But now I have to focus on myself and hand off responsibilities to others which is hard. I might be a bit of a perfectionist, which I hate that's so not my vibe haha. I also had very strict parents growing up, both type A, raised by immigrant parents, enforcing strict Slavic mentalities. I'm trying to break the cycle of inter-generational trauma, which has caused a lot of tension in my household but I know it'll be worth it in the long run.

I had to fight for my title and pay in my current job. I'm only 24, one of the youngest on my team and I constantly feel like I have to prove myself. One of my bosses is great, we are very friendly and rant to each other quite a lot, but she can also be quite mean and micromanagey when she's stressed. I work 9am-5pm, technically supposed to have an hour in unpaid breaks but I inevitably work the 8h day without a break, if not more than that. Free labour! I'm a workaholic, fuelled by stress and deadlines. My workplace is also a bit negative, and I'm incredibly burnt out, so I'm currently struggling a bit with motivation and optimism. I used to be the type of person who was delusionally optimistic, to trick my unconscious mind into believing anything. Now, I'm pessimistic, waiting to put out the next fire at work. I hate it! I wish I had that spark and lust for life that I had before graduating.

I'm also perhappppsss a bit depressed, but it's winter in Canada so you can't blame me! I just work a lot and don't do a lot of things for myself so combined with a negative work situation is less than ideal.

Perhaps other relevant things about me, I'm a big mediator, an ambivert leaning more on the introverted side, and an empath. I tend to feel others' feelings and pain as if it were my own, something I used to pride myself on but I've had to suppress it a bit since my workplace can be cut and dry. Also in the coming weeks, I have a couple interviews with some potential grad school supervisors, submitting final revisions for my manuscript, and I'll be submitting my last grad school application for my dream school. There's a lot of uncertainty, will I get accepted? will this professor like me? I hate it!! Super stressful, and my imposter syndrome is rampant. Also, the last time I took the MCAT I basically failed, so I really need to study efficiently and make some progress.

Some interesting questions to ask me throughout the study: what is your stress level, are you feeling optimistic or pessimistic, was today a good or bad day, were you a good boss today, did you feel listened to/heard today? Also, don't be afraid to ask me something funny? I love a good meme, thought-provoking prompt, something to distract me from my boring stressful life!

In summary, I'm a highly stressed and anxious almost mid-20 year old feeling very lost navigating my life. I often feel like I'm not heard or taking up too much space, and don't have a good sense of a middle ground. I have lots of deadlines coming up, and its time to really focus on MCAT studying and grad school, but it's hard to separate myself from a job that consumes me. I'm learning to care for myself and bring a little joy into my life because I deserve it!? I'm scatterbrained (clearly), and learning to find my place as a silly little gen z lady in a rigid professional world. I do have plans to go out with my friends over the next few weekends, which will be interesting during this hectic month. We'll see how it goes, fingers crossed I can gain some insight in this study and help you do your research :)

name: Miranda Zhu
GenItems_narr:
I am a night owl so I usually go to sleep late, get in bed around 12:15am and actually sleep at 12:35-45am. I go to sleep very fast and have no insomnia. The above apply for normal school days, if I have no early class the next day, I would go to sleep later. I usually wake up at 10:30am. I don't usually eat breakfast, some crackers if I really need to. I feel energetic during early morning class, but usually after that I would start to feel sleepy. I need a power nap around 1.5h if I have early class. I usually feels sleepy after dinner, probably because of food coma. 

My mental state is usually very stable, except for few circumstances. I get stress and feel anxious when my roommate is doing homework because I feel like I'm lagging and get peer pressured from it. I also get mad for no reason when I didn't accomplish anything in a long period of time ex. can't solve math problems, can't do the right coding. I'm also very sentimental before my menstrual cycle.

name: Taylor Hsieh
GenItems_narr:
I'm definitely a night owl; getting up in the morning is so difficult, even if it's later in the day. I get a bit sluggish after meals. Only when I'm around a bunch of white people do I feel out of place because I'm Asian. It's something I've become less self-conscious of as I've gotten older. Even though I want to become an immigration lawyer, I become very stressed out on Tuesdays and Thursdays when I have my Writing in Law class because my professor is very stringent and no-nonsense. I miss my home friends from high school often- they're very similar to me in being mostly Chinese, nerdy, musically inclined, and conservative in terms of behavior. 

I often feel lonely throughout the day, as I spend most of it alone and not talking to people. I'm an introvert and go to class by myself, eat alone, and study the best by myself. I try to get myself to go to more public places though to be more productive. When I go out to a party or something on Friday or Saturday night, I often feel guilty for spending time socializing and not buckling down. I feel guilty about a lot of things. I feel guilty for not practicing my violin more and letting my private lessons in the past go to waste. I'm proud of the fact I've started to read very frequently again as a hobby.

name: Sukhneet Toor
GenItems_narr:
I like stability in my life. I try to stick to the same schedule every day, for example, by starting with a workout, going to work, and then coming home cooking dinner. From here, I have some structure for my daily life, and then I can adjust based on other commitments or needs. Like if I need to schedule an "off day" from working out, or if there's a work outing on a weeknight. This helps me to make time for things that are important, like work or health/fitness. If I have too many other commitments being scheduled around these, I start to feel burnout, which can break down the whole system. When this happens I simplify my schedule back down to the basics until I am consistent with those activities again, before I try to add any extra activities. 

I worry about the future. Recent events have thrown off my expectations for my future. I've had some positive changes but some others are negative. I worry about my future relationship with my siblings and parents. I also worry about the strength of my friendships and my ability to make new connections (something I have always found difficult, but after coming out of lockdown and practicing human interaction I feel a little bit better about it). I'm realizing that this paragraph is actually about relationships, but I'll add that I also worry about the next stages in my life, and how they will affect my relationships. Like, will I like my sisters-in-law? Will that affect the connection that my brothers and I have? Will I find my life partner? Will they be accepted by the other important people in my life?

I want to get connected with my roots. Growing up I always rejected my culture, but since working in community health, I've really wanted to re-enter my own community. Over the past year, I've realized a few things that may have contributed to my decision to ignore my heritage. I was bullied by a few of my peers from a very young age, who were of the same ethnicity as me. They bullied me at community gatherings (No issue now, it's been a long time, and we have mutual friends I shouldn't have let it bother me). I think I began to deliberately seek out friendships with people of other ethnicities or groups thinking I would have a better chance at being accepted. Another thing was that I felt out of place with my cousins. My younger brother, myself, and a cousin of ours are the only family members born in the states. My cousins, who spoke our language fluently, would tease me for my American accent and poor vocabulary and pronunciation, so I would refuse to participate in conversations or practice the language until a few years ago.
GenItems_Unique_item_10: get connected with my cultural roots

name: Yimeng Luo
GenItems_narr:
I usually feel tired when I get up early. Actually, if I can, I usually sleep twelve hours a day: from 1 A.M. to 1 P.M. Unfortunately, I have two courses in the morning at this quarter. I need to get up at 6:30 A.M. for education course and 8:30 A.M. for ballet course. I am easy to get tired, but when I saw something I am interested in, I don't want to sleep any more. 

I have hard time to focus on something. I am really easy to be distracted. 

I love to hang out with my friends, and I am so happy to play with them. However, if I have to play with someone, I knew but not my friend, I will exhausted. I love to make new friends, but I know if we will be friends or not in a few meetings. Therefore, if I knew someone, like we are classmates in the high school, but we are not friends. Then, it's hard to be friends in the future.

I like playing games! Game world is so cool and so fantastic. I hope the technic in the future could lead me into the world.

My emotions are easily tugged by my close friends or families. I think they are important and they can influence my emotions easily.

name: Taranya Balamurugan
GenItems_narr:
I am generally an introverted person, but I open up more to people and actually become more talkative as I get to know them. I often seek out close-knit individual friendships or smaller friend groups. I do not do well in larger groups of social situations. I often expect people to approach me first.

I find that I am pretty good at managing stress, I do not take on more than I can handle and will never overwork myself. But I acknowledge that I work hard and will always get my work done.

I find that I am tired a lot of the time, especially at the end of the day when I get back from classes. I spend a lot of my free time on my phone/laptop watching tv or scrolling through social media.

name: Veronica Lee
GenItems_narr:
I wake up every morning doing my best to fulfill my duties as a student. When I feel stressed (less than three times a week), I would buy food that I crave and just enjoy the moment I have with the food item. When I am in class, I usually sit in one of the few rows in the back because I feel less "exposed" to people. I've been trying to sit closer to the front, but it feels intimidating to me and my face usually gets red. It could be that back in middle school and high school, I would wear hoodies in class because it felt safe and comfortable. Since it would look weird doing so in college, maybe sitting in the back is comfortable. Another reason that might contribute to why I like sitting in the back is that I am self-conscious about my hair from the back.

Last quarter, I had all morning classes, so I would come back and sit at the dining table all day doing work. It was super boring and felt like a waste of time somehow. So this quarter, I decided to take five classes and do an internship. I feel way more productive and satisfied now. I would rather take up more workload than be bored and waste my time relaxing too often. Doing so makes me feel like I have a purpose in life. I generally don't have any personal issues at home, friends, money, or school; I enjoy them all. Maybe because my life is not too crazy, I need to make my life more interesting by adding workload to myself and feeling what others feel.

I would describe myself as an introvert. Sometimes I would feel fine talking to non-awkward people, but not too talkative people. When I talk to people, I generally would like to stay away from super talkative people and people who do not initiate and reciprocate conversations. I easily get tired when talking to talkative people and I get stressed and awkward when trying to discuss with people who do not reciprocate conversations. Small conversations also make me uncomfortable because my mind goes blank.

name: Kathy Gutierrez
GenItems_narr:
Weekends are great for me since that's when I have the freest time to myself. I play video games, spend time talking to my boyfriend through discord, clean, and sometimes go to downtown for Dutch bros or other small treats for myself. It's wonderful knowing I have no obligations at that time. 

I am a homebody I greatly dislike going outside as it makes me nervous since I have social anxiety. However, going outside is a necessity so I do my best to distract myself from those feelings by listening to music or trying to admire nature around me. Most of my life is fairly uneventful as I spend most of my time at home speaking to my boyfriend, watching horror movies, or playing video games.

Monday through Friday I work as an after-school site director for an elementary school. It's about 20-25 hours a week I work this job. I enjoy the work as the kids at my school site are very kind and sometimes draw me or other little cute things. I place these drawings in a folder and hang them up on my fridge. I change them up occasionally. I enjoy talking to the kids as they inspire me to do better things with my life. They are so kind and helpful to each other (most of the time). My boss can be mean sometimes which causes me a great deal of stress since I hate disappointing others and wish to do the best I can for my job and the kids I am working with. 

I try to call my mother and father at least once a week as they always make me happy to talk to them. I am just forgetful on when to call them.

I also do studies often to help me make money on the side, but also because I greatly enjoy doing studies. They help other people and seeing results is always fairly interesting. It helps me learn about other people and gain new experiences in life I otherwise wouldn't have. It's a fun thing to do Monday through Friday as that's usually when most studies are done.  

My life generally lacks structure since I tend to go with the flow on many things in my day to day. Sometimes I have a hard time getting out of bed to do my day as I feel I have nothing to do but in reality, I do have many things to do and occupy myself with getting started on that is the hard part. 

I like writing, drawing, sewing, reading, gaming, and film (mostly horror as I'm a horror nut). I like talking to people about my or their interest's passion is fun to see on other people's faces. 

Hope this is all helpful!

name: Yi-Ting Chua
GenItems_narr: I usually wake up still wanting more sleep. I always try to get at least 7 hours of sleep, so I am not sure why I feel that way. Could be that my quality of sleep is not that great most of the time. I usually prefer a small group of friends over a larger group. I like having a close relationship with a few friends. I often find it hard to speak up especially in a large group or in class, which is why I often worry a lot when classes have participation points involved. It is most likely that I am scared of saying the wrong thing or that what I say is to stupid. I guess it is more like scared of being judged. But usually when I am with my few friends who I am comfortable with, I always say what’s on my mind, although I do think before I speak. I am quite an energetic person but my social battery does go down pretty fast. I enjoy being alone but I also enjoy having company. I love staying at home and I enjoy just relaxing.

name: Britney Zientara
GenItems_narr:
I wake up every morning as early as I can because I work remotely for a company in another state, but I hit snooze a lot and don't really feel awake until the sun rises. I work pretty standard hours, but I just got my first salaried position and I really enjoy the work itself so I'm starting to try to be more flexible about time-- letting myself have breakfast even if I hit snooze too many times, taking a long lunch after a client was particularly abrasive, taking breaks for appointments, etc. Just as often, I find myself logging on in the late evening because I want to get the work done while I'm thinking about it and it has my interest rather than waiting for the next working day. I hate having my webcam on during meetings but I do really love interacting with clients and getting to say things like "my clients" or "I'm all booked up but I should have an opening XXX"; getting to sound so #professional and getting paid and treated like an expert in my field is even more exciting when I'm doing it in my Naruto pajamas with a cat in my lap and three empty energy drinks on the bar behind me. 

A lot of my life is centered around work, and it's really only a fluke that I wound up in a field I'm excited about and good at. I'm excruciatingly aware that early intimate experiences of the connection between American capitalism, housing instability, and food scarcity make concepts like "work/life balance" feel more abstract than the reality of high rent, higher medical bills, and a fully disabled partner, so I know I tend towards burnout and have to be very careful not to let myself cater to financial anxiety in the short-tem at the cost of long-term consequences to my physical and mental health. I experience chronic pain and fatigue, but my partner is sweet and wonderful and supportive and after I was diagnosed I focused all of my energy on getting a job that I could eventually do from home. After work and on weekends I play video games and spend time with my person and our cats, and overall I think I'm pretty happy.
GenItems_Unique_item_19: treated like an expert in my field

name: Clare Wang
GenItems_narr:
I am typically low energy for most of the day. On days I go to classes, I nap at every opportunity. When I don't go to classes, I sleep at around 7 am and wake up as late as 4 pm. I eat once a day around 5 pm. This is probably due to severe depression, although I refuse to take my prescribed antidepressants because I don't like how they make me feel. I try to work out twice a week, although I don't think I truly enjoy it. It's more a matter of trying to hate myself less. 
When I am awake, I spend a lot of time thinking about my mental state and life. Recurring thoughts include my troubles with interpersonal relationships, how others perceive me, and personal flaws. Interactions with other people occupy a significant portion of my worries. Just a brief encounter with someone at the door will have me anxious for hours. I often imagine scenarios in which I don't struggle as much forming and maintaining relationships with others. 
I'm in my best state at night. I often go out on walks at 3 am. I think they help my mental health, so I go even when weather conditions are not ideal.

name: Antonino Conte
GenItems_narr:
My daily routine is something that I like to plan out. For exmaple, most days I know the exact time I will be waking up and going to sleep to get up to 9 hours of sleep. Beyond that I plan which classes I will be working on for what days and at what times. Meal are also planned ahead of time so that I can cook for myself and clean in an efficient manner so as to not waste time. I like planning out everything because it means I can predict at the very least what my actions throughout the day will be. When I can't predict anything that will happen in a day is when I sometimes get anxiety.
Other things that I do every day is make sure to either eat a late big breakfast and skip lunch or eat a smaller breakfast so then I have space for lunch and dinner. Because I live in sacramento I get up around 1.5 to 2 hours ahead of my first class so I have time to get up, change, cook, brush my teeth, and any other morning things before drving twenty minutes to school. I also tend to listen to podcasts on my drives such as the Joe Rogan Show since I enjoy how he talks to people of many beliefs and views. After I get to school I tend to park in one of the back parking lots and then bike around the UC Davis campus. I like to bring my bike because because it allows me to park in areas that always have parking plus get from class to class easier. After that I do my classes and hw for the rest of the day while mixing in hanging out with friends. I obviously prefer the hanging out part but this quarter my classes have been mostly enjoyable. Except math, but that's because my professor is possibly the worst lecturer I've had including my elementary teachers. Beyond that I have really been enjying all my classes especially since the professors seem to really enjoy they're subjects and it comes out in their teaching.
GenItems_Unique_item_4: I listened to a good podcast

name: Amanda Augustine
GenItems_narr:
I typically feel a little bit anxious/overwhelmed at the start of my day, especially M-F when I'm thinking ahead about busy days at work. 
I work long days on Wednesdays, so those are typically the days each week that I feel the most overwhelmed. 
I usually am in the best mood on Fridays which is probably because I only work a half day and am looking forward to the weekend.
I am very family oriented and spending time with my family typically puts me in a really good.
I am an extrovert for the most part but there are definitely times when I enjoy having my own personal space and doing things independently. 
I have a cup of coffee every morning and definitely need this to get through the day. 
I haven't been in my current position at work for very long, so I have a strong sense of imposter syndrome and self-doubt that contributes to my feelings of stress at work. 
Sometimes I think that life feels too short to be doing the same daily routine every day (waking up, going to work, coming home, going to bed, and doing it all again the next day). For this reason, I feel the best when I am able to add some excitement/out of the ordinary activities into my week. 
Sometimes I struggle with mild symptoms of dissociation which I'm able to cope with pretty well overall. 
I have two cats and spending time with them makes me feel very happy. 
I struggle with body image concerns and think about this a lot, but I'm trying to practice self-love and body neutrality.
I live in NY state and don't really enjoy the cold, so this time of year is a lot less enjoyable for me than the warmer months when I can adventure/be outside/be more active.

name: Esha Biju
GenItems_narr:
I am usually very outgoing and want to be surrounded by people all the time. However often I feel like I have to try or put in a lot of effort for people to like me. I overthink a lot and I feel like many people tend not to understand me. In all honestly, I feel like no one understands me except me. Everyday I have such different moods to the point where I think i have BPD. I often feel like my energy and how I feel is affected by the way people treat me throughout the day. If something bad happens, I also let this ruin my whole day.

When I have a test or interview, or something that is giving me a lot of anxiety- I tend to not be able to focus on anything as much because that is all I think about. This affects my daily life as there are many things that scares me but I just spent my time thinking about the future that I forget to live in the present.
GenItems_Unique_item_6: Thinking about the future I forget to live in the present
GenItems_Unique_item_9: If something bad happens I let it ruin my whole day

name: Nalia Nechayev
GenItems_narr:
I wake up early every day because I like to have the freedom that offers before classes start. I get ready have breakfast, get coffee, and do homework. This brings me a sense of peace. I like the routine of getting up early and doing the same thing in the morning, such as eating the same thing, going to the same place, and doing the same tasks. As a person, I am definitely on the introverted side and prefer to spend time alone. When I am around people my social battery gets used up quicker than an outgoing person's would so I limit my social events. I am a part of a ministry team on campus because I believe in God and his son Jesus who died to save us. I chose this to be my extracurricular because my beliefs align with the people I spend time with. During the week I have bible study, a ministry meeting, and an event that are all associated with the club. I tend to feel particularly drained with the events that end late such as 8-10 pm. During the week I have classes that start between 9-11 am and end at 12 - 2 pm usually, then on Thursdays, I have lab. I find it harder to focus in lab because it lasts till 4 and is 2hrs. During the week I meet up one on one with people to talk about general things like school, faith, and life. I limit these meetings from 2-3 per week. I like these meetings because when I am focused on school I find I do not devote time to building relationships with people. During the weekend I spend time with my close friends. We go to church on Sundays, and the rest of the weekend we are either studying at coffee shops, shopping for necessities, or hanging out. These meetings are different than social outings because I do not feel tired of spending time with these people. 

My religion and my education are the main drives in my life. I tend to not self big goals for myself because in college they are always shifting based on the influx of information. I find that in college I am very particular about the people I spend time with and the things I do. I am not friends with my current roommates and do not spend unnecessary time with them, I prefer to have the room to myself actually and do not feel at ease when they are there. I find I am most productive when studying by myself somewhere not in my room. As a person I tend to identify as creative, so apart from my religion and studies I write, whether in general or poetry, I create art, whether digital or the regular hands-on kind, and things like nail art, hairstyles, fashion, or creating business ideas. Mood wise I would not say I am a cheerful person but I am not a sad or angry person either. My mood tends to stay the same but I am much more chatty with people who I have things in common with. I find it challenging in life when I think I can accomplish more than I am capable of. I also find it challenging to set myself goals that I know will benefit me but are draining with school and club activities on top. By this, I mean waking up early and exercising to then go to sleep late finishing school work which takes away from sleep. Sleep is a big thing in my life, I do not have trouble sleeping, and I tend to feel I cannot function if I do not get an adequate amount.

name: Lauren Remish
GenItems_narr:
Most days I wake up and it takes me some time to actually get out of bed. I never really dread class, luckily I have friends in all my classes. I then usually meet up with other friends after/between classes. Sometimes I get a little insecure walking into the coho because I feel like all eyes are on me. Which I know is the spotlight effect and I definitely should've outgrown that by now but I haven't. I then go home, back dinner, and hangout with my roommates.

I can be a little moody and snappy, mostly with my roommates. This is usually when I am tired or hungry. I like being around people like all the time. Whenever I am alone and I tend to get in my head and spiral about the little things. Sometimes it's hard for me to fall asleep at night because I am too busy overthinking. I usually will go on tik tok and then toss and turn for a bit and then fall asleep. That is a pretty typical day.

name: Becca Paskowitz
GenItems_narr:
I have a very busy and unpredictable schedule. I am commuting from Davis to the Bay Area some days. Other days, I work from home. Generally, I am the most energized during the morning and can get a bit slower after lunch. 

I enjoy my fast-paced work life. However, sometimes I am unable to relax to the extent I would want. I feel like there is seldom enough time in the day to do everything I want. I am an extrovert who generally gets energy from others.

name: Lauren Godfrey
GenItems_narr:
I think life gets very mundane going to work everyday. I don't particularly enjoy my job because it's a lot of copy and pasting, but I do excited to see my coworker when I go into the office. It is hard for me to get motivated to find a new job because when I get home from work, I just feel like watching tv or going on my phone. Right now, I am struggling because my boyfriend just broke up with me, but was not really open to communicating about it. I really don't like conflict and so this has been very hard for me knowing that we did not end on the best terms. I also don't like cutting people out of my life and it's been really hard for me to cut off all contact. It makes me feel like a bad person. 

I am someone who has anxiety, but I have gotten better at managing it. What makes me nervous most, is the unknown. I like to feel like I have control. However, at the same time, I have been described as "a very go with the flow" type of person. I think this is in part because I would rather avoid conflict and going with the flow often achieves this. I generally get along with all types of people and I have a lot of friends whom I would consider all to be pretty close friends. I like feeling like I have a lot of friends to talk to, and each one is there for me in a different way. I'm also really close with my family and so living in a different state than them can make me sad, especially when I have just seen them and I have to go back to living my own life. 

I am a pretty optimistic person and generally in a very good mood. However, after I graduated college, I have been feeling a bit lost in what direction my life will take since it feels like I have so much freedom. I also want to feel like my career has purpose and meaning and so that is something I am searching for.

name: Kaitlyn Engelhart
GenItems_narr:
I get really nervous and stressed before all of my classes. Most days, I don't know where to start which can really affect me emotionally. I am getting less sleep and feel more emotional than normal. I am just starting graduate school and it really very over-whelming, especially as a first-generation college student. My best friend from undergrad is no longer in the program, so I feel very alone and like an outcast. I feel this way more in my classes versus in the grad resource room because there some of the students in the cohort above me will talk to me more. 
    When I come home, I often feel like I am missing out on things with my roommates. However, at least once a week I cook with one of my roommates and I always feel better after that because we try something out together and talk about our days throughout the process. 
    On the weekends, I usually feel relief in going home for a little bit but also guilt that I am not with my roommates or doing homework. It is a nice drive though and it normally clears my head and I feel better afterwards.

name: Jasmine Greer
GenItems_narr:
What I think about on the daily: 

My days tend to vary a lot when it comes to my thought processes. Some days I am extremely motivated and excited, while others no matter how hard I try to get out of bed and be productive I just can't. I don't think I am Bipolar, but more just burnt out. 

I think about my future a lot. Where I am going, how am I going to afford anything, if my parents are thinking about me, if they are proud of me, if my dog misses me, etc. It can get pretty random at times. I spend a lot of time talking to myself in my head and talking myself through things. I tend to be very emotional and can think about the things that affect me emotionally for days to months to weeks on end. 

I think a lot about the way people think of me. I am sure many people feel the same way, but I don't feel very conventional. In a lot of ways- whether it be the way I look, think, act, dress, etc. I faced a pretty big identity crisis a couple years ago, but I think I am starting to get the hang of things now and accepting of my differences. 

I tend to see my boyfriend a lot. He is a best friend to me and helps me with a lot of life stuff. He is very resourceful with cars and handy work and always helps me whenever he can. He has a very kind heart and is a genuinely good-hearted person. I think he probably understands me more than anyone else.

I have a few pretty close friends who I see throughout the week. They are good hearted people. They make me laugh a lot and I can appreciate that. I lost a good friend a few years ago. She did not pass away or anything, but did something pretty unforgivable and selfish. She never reached out after or apologized. I think about this about daily too. 

I do not have any courses in my schedule which ruin my mood. This quarter I actually love my classes and they interest me. I look forward to them.

Let me know if you need any other information!
GenItems_Unique_item_1: My days tend to vary a lot
GenItems_Unique_item_3: I think a lot about the way people think of me
GenItems_Unique_item_4: I tend to be very emotional
GenItems_Unique_item_5: I spend a lot of time talking to myself in my head
GenItems_Unique_item_6: They make me laugh a lot
GenItems_Unique_item_8: I do not have any courses which ruin my mood
GenItems_Unique_item_9: Helps me with a lot of life stuff
GenItems_Unique_item_10: If they are proud of me

name: Mary Moneypenny
GenItems_narr:
I can’t type very well because of Parkinson’s disease symptoms (tremors and periodic high blood pressure with racing heart beats, especially st night, more when I am trying to play my songs on my digital piano, which is getting more difficult for me every day.  I’m gradually losing my ability to play songs that I have written but for which I have never received any compensation, except the satisfaction of having a couple of songs publicly performed.  

One starts:

There is promise in the dawn,.,.

I tell myself that every evening just to keep going…
I think it begins with A432 hz, which is supposed to help with Parkinson’s symptoms, according to one website I saw.  Chanting “uOms” .   st A 432 hz is supposed to do that, as, but I don’t chant (but I like the disco song “Let’s All Chant!”  It picks up my spirits!)

I feel so sad about my song’s dying with me because I believe that If God gives you a gift, God is collaborating with you and through you, God’s creativity is expressed.  So I feel that I have to share my gift with others, if possible.  I feel that music can possibly change the world for the better, and that’s what I hope to do.  The guy who did the musical notation for that Hymn said it was “inspired” — he said that about only one other song that I wrote (I’ve written about 30 so far)..  

Parkinson’s is supposed to be a progressively debilitating disease, so it is difficult to maintain a positive mental attitude, especially with the various physical and mental conditions that accompany the disease (like constipation, anxiety, depression, difficulty walking the dog).  

Exercise is supposed to help alleviate some of the stress associated with the symptoms.  So I make myself exercise every day, if possible.  However, I mostly find myself going back to bed for an hour or so after breakfast— maybe because my sleep is so disturbed and disrupted by having to get up to pee several times a night, drinking water because my night guard that’s supposed to keep me from grinding my teeth creates a dry mouth condition. So it’s like a vicious cycle.  

I have to go take my RYTARY and melatonin now.  Time to “hit the sack.”

I’ll have to try to finish the survey in the morning, because “After all, tomorrow is another day!”  (Per Scarlett O’Hara of “GWTW” fame—I hear tho music as accompaniment.)

CIAO for now!

name: Yousheng Wang
GenItems_narr: Occasional anxiety. Cursing and screaming a lot when I am alone due to stress. Most of the day feeling tired and lack motivation. Masturbate about twice a week to reduce stress. Tuesday ruins my mood because I have discussion from 6pm-9pm. Try to have normal sleep schedule, but sometimes browses my phone till 1-3am. Some what of a nihilist. Low self-esteem. Saturday always lighten mood because have board game session with friends. Highly ambitious and overbearing. Often overthinks things for hours. Very fickle. Sometimes goes to the gym about once a week, which lightens the mood. Keep a journal and read books everyday. Somewhat fearful of homework. Really scared of being overwhelmed by it.

name: Lorelei Kilmer
GenItems_narr: I am an introverted person yet I like to give my best when I am around people energy wise. I am anxious so while many things daily tasks like going to school and work may not stress me out inner thoughts do. I feel anxious about trying to be on time, drive people around, get to my classes, study and have a good attitude while doing so. I usually wake up early 5 or 6 will have some time to myself to read the Bible and journal then I will either work out or get ready and I'm out the door to either class a meeting or my work. I'm usually in class in between work and meeting and don't get home till around 6 or 7 make a quick dinner and workout if I didn't that morning. Maybe call my parents or I have an after dinner commitment I have to go to. Most days I'm pretty exhausted or tired but yet feel proud that I accomplished and did so much. During the day I am usually rushing around so my brain is usually go, go, go yet I do ten to do a lot of deep thinking on top of thinking of my day to day tasks and responsibilities. I also like to try and meet up with people one on one for coffee or dinner when I can. I want to make people throughout my day feel loved and special and appreciated. I try to manage my time while yet prioritizing others usually eating all meals on the go. My weekends are booked to usually with studying or driving friends to all these different stores

name: Shyann Hoang
GenItems_narr: My daily life for the most part revolves around work and school. During the week, my schedule starts with school then it switches back and forth with work each day. I try to keep the timing of my schedules later into the day because I’m not a morning person. Early mornings are almost impossible for me, especially since I’ve never been very good at getting out of bed to begin with. I am definitely a huge night owl as well as a homebody. If I’m not working or doing schoolwork, I’m most likely at home. I enjoy relaxing in the comforts of my home with my cat. The most social interaction I get is probably with my boyfriend when he is home from college.

name: Yixuan Li
GenItems_narr:
I am usually tired from Monday to Thursday since I need to get up early to work as a tutor. Most of the time I do not have time for breakfast so I can be very hungry in the morning. Being a tutor is a challenging job and I can be really nervous as well. I usually get sleepy after lunch. So i drink coffee to keep me awake. 

In the afternoon, I study with others on a research project and we will do the data analysis work everyday.  However, most of the time I am quite motivated with peers around because I don't want to be left behind others.  Every evening I watch tv series for one hour or two to relax. Then I will take a shower, which will make me feel refreshed and have more energy. I will review the research work and also prepare for the next day's tutoring material. It can be hard for me to fall asleep because i can be immersed in Tiktok and do not want to sleep. That will make me hard to get up the next day, and I am trying to get rid of this bad habit.

name: Connor Bondoc
GenItems_narr:
My day starts usually around 9 AM unless I have an earlier class but this quarter none of my classes are too early. I'm not usually a morning person but I really enjoy going to the gym in the morning because it makes me feel more energized for the rest of the day and it's more than a hobby for me, so it puts me in a good mood. It also helps me feel like I have accomplished something early in the morning already. Later I go to all my classes which don't necessarily put me in a really good mood because I am the type of person who can't really sit through things well. I always want to be doing something or seeing something very interesting. In other words, I get bored easily. After my classes, I will do homework. Usually, around 3-4 PM I will get tired after doing homework for a bit so I will eat lunch and then take a nap or rest and hang out with friends for a bit or just take a break. If I have any more homework to do, I will finish it and play video games which always puts me in a good mood. It's a really good way for me to relieve stress. I usually eat dinner around 9 PM and go to bed around 11-12.

In my classes this quarter so far, I often find that I will never be friends with my classmates, due to their personalities, interests, and groups. I have never really found they I have anything in common with them. Truth be told, sometimes they irritate me. When I am at home resting or have free time, I really enjoy watching skiing/snowboarding videos because that's also a passion I have. Usually I watch anything that is outside or involves someone being active because I always want to be pushing my body and trying new things. I don't really have unwanted thoughts or behaviors and I count myself lucky because my mood doesn't change much throughout the day unless something bad happens.

name: yuetong gong
GenItems_narr:
I don't regard myself as an energetic person. Most of the time I feel peaceful with my daily routine. Usually, I easily get tired when I have some socialization with others. For example, talking with my friends for more than two or three hours in total a day makes me have a sore thoartdon't want to say a single word. 

I hardly get up early and am kind of struggling with this habit, as it makes me think that I sleep too long every day and squeeze my time to do things I want to do. When I occasionally manage to get up earlier, I will find myself very effective and organized on that day.

name: Kieran Kim
GenItems_narr: I generally do my best to fit to a specific schedule that I make sure to lay out before each quarter. I have all my classes, their exact times, and locations saved on my personal calendar that I reference to multiple times a day. This in conjunction with alarms for morning, bus arrivals, class reminders, and extracurricular activities help me stay on top of everything. I mostly do this out of necessity as I'm quite forgetful, and if I don't have it written down on my calendar, I'll likely forget to do it. Because of this, I would say that I have a fairly stable lifestyle that does not have many downs, but most certainly has its ups when I interact with friends, set aside time for hobbies I enjoy, such as games, knitting, or reading, etc. I'd say my sleep is also fairly consistent as I regularly get at least seven hours of sleep unless I have an important assignment that I've been neglecting. I cook every single day for myself and some of my housemates, which I enjoy about 90% of the time. The rest sometimes feels like a chore but does not usually bother me more than that day. I think the thing that would make my mood depress would be if I feel that others around me are upset in some way. I generally do my best to either let them rant to me or give them space, but I definitely "catch their vibe" a lot. I would say overall I'm a fairly positive and neutral person.

name: Anli Ji
GenItems_narr: I get excited whenever professors assign me hard calculation/ logic thinking problems and feel happy if I solve them correctly before others. I get bored if someone is talking with a plain/calm voice. I prefer to stay on my own and enjoy some quiet time/ meditation every day when I get home. I get tired after biking for more than 20 min. I get nervous talking to new people, but I am willing to present myself and express my thoughts thoroughly whenever necessary. I always feel anxious before group hangouts with my friends, overthink the worst outcomes, and purposely prepare common interests/ topics to share before the meetup. I love gardening and being surrounded by bees. Nature will make me genuinely happy.
GenItems_Unique_item_1: solving logical or heavy calculation problems

name: Walter jakes
GenItems_narr: i am very energetic around positive energy .i vibe with anyone who comes my way when i feel their aura is right

name: Grace Wiley
GenItems_narr:
I am generally a very positive person who lives a busy life as a law student, part-time worker, and also a social human being. I feel excited to wake up, either to relax in my bed and hang out with my dog for a bit before afternoon classes or to head to the gym and get a productive workout in before morning classes. I find myself happiest when I am with other people, whether that be in classes, going on walks, or hanging out after class. There are some periods on Tuesdays and Thursdays when I spend the afternoons alone, doing my part-time work as a TA and grader. These times tend to feel the most robotic in going through the motions, but I don't feel entirely negative about them, as they are necessary. 

My energy levels range throughout the day, usually with more in the mornings. However, by keeping busy, I generally stay fairly energetic throughout the day, except during those periods when I am working alone in which I am more going through the motions. At night, I am also by myself, but it feels different because I am relaxing after a long day, surrounded by family and my dog. 

Weekends are spent by myself, with my boyfriend, and/or with friends. I like having a variety of options of activities such that I am able to choose which one I am feeling based on my energy mood. Typically, I enjoy spending a day to myself to catch up, and another with friends.
GenItems_Unique_item_6: Happiest when I am with other people
GenItems_Unique_item_10: I like having a variety of options of activities

name: Chieh-Hsi （Jessie)
GenItems_narr: I usually feel calm throughout the whole day and I'm always tired in the morning when I have to get out of bed and sometimes at night around 7 PM, but it's not like very sleepy, it's just like feeling going on with the day without being perfectly energetic. I feel busy with what I need to do like there is a bunch of lists of things waiting for me to do, but on Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday, and Sunday I have Taekwondo practice that kinda boosts up my mood. I'm the club officer of the Taekwondo club and being with other officers makes me feel in comfort zone. It might be because we know each other since last year (freshman year) and they are the only people that I'll be social with the most as an international student out here in the States studying abroad. I could get calmer when being with them because they are very chill and funny. However, as a student, I have to study and I did not really do well in the last quarter. I felt the pressure of it and I have to pull up the GPA which I know it's my responsibility and I don't want to let my parents down.

name: Matthew Kissell
GenItems_narr: Most days, I wake up super late in the day unless I have one of my morning classes which are on Tuesday and Thursdays. I am a complete night-owl and morning person. Mondays and Fridays I feel completely fine because I have only one class which is very easy but I do all of my work for the week on Monday and some of it spills into Tuesday. I have less social interaction on Monday compared to other days simply because I do all of my work but I still hang out with my friends in the dorm after midnight. Almost every night I stay up until at least 1:30am either watching a movie or just talking to my friends. I fit in well with my friends but I think that I have a weird tendency to want to be everyone's favorite subconsciously. Thursdays also suck because I have my most classes and a lab from 7pm-10pm. Weekends do get a little repetitive but I think that I am very good at making my own fun and being fine with being alone. I don't usually take naps during the day but I do try to go the gym everyday of the week but it is usually more like 4-5 days a week. Sometimes a do get tired of being around people during the day so I will go on a walk alone late at night not for any goal in particular but just because. I can't describe it specifically but I sometimes I just need to do it.

name: Aashima Verma
GenItems_narr:
I am currently working a full time job in Finance. I feel alright about my work, it isn't very exciting nor it is very boring. It is mostly work from home but I do go to office once or twice a week. I am a person who likes to keep to oneself so I am not a fan of going to office in-person. I don't go out much as I like to stay home more often. I generally have very low energy through out the day but I try to get as much as possible work done since I aspire to be a responsible adult. Sometimes I do feel overwhelmed with the amount of things that are going on in my mind at the same time but I try my best to overcome.
I believe I am an evening person as I dread waking up early in the morning but have the most energy during the evening. I wish my job had the flexibility to work in the evenings but due to the nature of the job, I can't do so. I try to eat healthy and home cooked food everyday but I also give into not eating as many fruits and vegetables due to lack of better meal planning.
I have very selective friends and I like to keep things mostly with myself. I have very loving parents whom I call almost everyday and we talk about our days. I am international student who came from across the world to get my education in the States and I have always felt a little out of place. But I have met quite a few people during my time in this country that I will probably never forget.

name: Chloe Lin
GenItems_narr:
For my daily life, I usually like being busy and occupying myself with things. Whenever I have free time, I get restless because I feel like I should be doing something instead of just relaxing. I am not a morning person, so my worst part of the day is whenever I wake up. It is hard for me to get out of the morning, but usually my mood lifts as I go about my day. Tuesdays and Wednesdays are my hardest days because I have classes/work all day. I find work particularly hard because even though it is a very easy job, it is a very boring one. I wish my job was more fulfilling, because I feel like I could do something better with my time. Overall, I get sad when I am not as productive as I should be. 

All in all, I still love being a college student though. Aside from classes and work, I spend lots of time with my friends. I feel two-faced a lot of the times, because I am pretty shy and reserved in class but sociable when I’m with people I’m comfortable with. I am trying to be more friendly with people that I meet in class, because I realize that my time here at college is limited. This may be the only time I am surrounded with so many people my age, so I want to give people a chance. It would be nice to make some friends outside of my usual social circle.

name: Nicole Wetzel
GenItems_narr:
I am the type of person that likes consistency and schedules and as soon as I get off my typical routine I get completely turned around. In the mornings I wake up and go straight to the gym. If I do not go, then I tend to feel somewhat unsatisfied and quite tired throughout the day. But when I do go, I feel energized and tend to get started on my work immediately after washing up (around 930-10). After that I would say most of the work that I have is fairly simple but when it comes to Mondays and Wednesdays, I have a completely free day besides a 3-4 lecture and it's either feel productive that I do enough work/studying that day or I feel absolutely no satisfaction and regret.
Recently I have been having feelings of inadequacy in compared to who I associate myself with. I have a fairly "smart" friend group and whenever I do study groups with them that's when I feel the worst. I feel as though I'm not up for the challenge and struggle to add anything into the conversation. Then when it comes to studying alone, I get frustrated because I don't know how to do a problem and don't have a resource (friend) readily available to help. A solution would be to attend office hours but I am still struggling to jump that hurdle of attending and asking a professor/TA for help.

name: Airiana Reyes-Gonzales
GenItems_narr:
On Mondays, I have a class at 7:30 am that leaves me exhausted for the entire day. Tuesdays and Thursdays I have most of my lectures. After my second one that ends at noon, I am exhausted, but I perk up after eating lunch. I eat dinner with my partner around 6 or 7:30 pm depending on the day which cheers up my mood. Most mornings I am tired, but I function. Fridays and the weekend is where I am the most energetic. 

In class, I typically rarely speak up unless needed. Usually they are good experiences with my peers, rarely I have issues. The few times I do, I still remain polite, but when class is over I end up ranting about my experiences to a friend, sibling, or my partner. I bike to and around school. Those times typically leave me irritated or stressed.

In these upcoming weeks, I have a long research project which may have me feeling quite stressed.
GenItems_Unique_item_1: class at seven thirty am and exhausted for entire day
GenItems_Unique_item_2: tuesdays and thursdays and exhausted and perk up after lunch
GenItems_Unique_item_3: dinner with my partner and cheers up my mood
GenItems_Unique_item_4: most mornings and tired but functioning
GenItems_Unique_item_5: Fridays and weekends and most energetic
GenItems_Unique_item_6: with peers and usually good experiences
GenItems_Unique_item_7: issues with peers and still polite
GenItems_Unique_item_8: after a class with peer issues and rant to friends siblings or partner
GenItems_Unique_item_10: upcoming weeks and long research paper and may be stressed in general

name: Dheera  Dusanapudi
GenItems_narr:
I'm usually pretty motivated and excited about my classes and my jobs--I work on campus as a researcher and off campus in food service. Some of my courses bore me a little bit, because they get too theoretical, but I refocus myself by remembering the career path I want after college and how important it is to me that I excel at it. 

Typically, I wake up in the morning, eat breakfast, head off to classes, do some homework, and then might have do some work. I really like to run, and I'm considering training for a half marathon, but for some reason it gets hard to motivate myself even though I know I love running when I'm actually doing it. 

I always like to hike and travel. I'm trying to save up money to go on a long distance hike this summer--I don't think I'll have enough, but that doesn't really bother me. I just want to do it before I graduate, because after graduation I feel like my life could go anywhere and I doubt I'll have the freedom I have now. Which is odd because I don't know if I really feel like I can do whatever I want right now either. 

In the next few weeks I'll mostly be working, going to class, and spending time with friends on the weekend, but I have a work trip too. Nowadays I feel really bored all the time. I feel like traveling or just being in a new situation is the only time I ever really feel like myself, or I guess feel like I like who I am.

name: Joyce Chung
GenItems_narr:
I am pretty tired most days, especially in the morning. I usually perk up when I'm with close friends and classmates. I like being around people I know, because I gain energy from being with them. In contrast, when I am feeling low in energy or down, I try not to show it too much or at least play it off as a joke because I don't want my friends to worry too much for me and see me in a positive light. 
My mood is pretty easily influenced, but I try to keep it in. I think that I put too much energy into people and not so much myself sometimes. It makes it hard when you put so much time into a person or people and it doesn't really get reciprocated. In that aspect, I think I get easily unmotivated and distracted when the people close to me seem to have no interest or me or don't reciprocate the energy I give off to them.

name: Fatima Rodriguez
GenItems_narr: I am a female who is currently a three year here at UC Davis. My mother is from Mexico and my father is from Spain. So I am half Mexican and half Spanish. I am Catholic and i an a strong believer. I hope to have a career in the medical field but I am not exactly sure what. At first I thought I wanted to be a nurse but now I’m not so sure. The future scares me but I hope to be successful. Being successful means have a great career where I can make enough money to be able to support my family and myself. Most days I just go through the motions of the day. I’m usually a very happy person but college took a toll on me. I currently don’t have any friends but I do have a boyfriend. When I’m with him I’m happy other than that I just go through the motions. I’m a first gen student so maneuvering the daily life of a college is still hard. It’s especially hard because my first year was during COVID so I didn’t get the opportunity to make friends or get the simple introductions of college life. I don’t have much of a social life because when I’m not at school or studying I’m at my job. Managing a job and school has been kind of stressful so this is why I just go through the motions on the daily basis. Also not having friends puts a damper on my social life and my every day activities. When I’m not at school or at work, I’m at home even on the weekends. I’m big on family but at the moment my mom and I aren’t on the best terms. I’m a little depressed because of the relationship I have with my mom. She means a lot to me but hasn’t been treating my boyfriend or I the best. She comments negative things about him. I sometimes get panic and anxiety attacks because of my fear of the future. If one thing that scares me more than anything it’s death and the future. I’m not big on things that I can’t control. I’m a big believer on fake it till you make it and hiding my emotions. No one really cares how you feel so why show them. I like hiding how I actually feel on a day to day bases behind a smile. I also believe that smiling makes others peoples day and even though my day is crappy there’s shouldn’t be. I am very competitive when it comes to sports and I am a huge sports fan. When a football game or baseball game, watching makes me really happy. Laughing is a coping mechanism for me. I even laugh when I’m sad or mad. Sometimes I can’t even control it. So overall I’m a happy person but currently I’m a student whole numb with all things college and my mother.

name: Izabelle Rubio
GenItems_narr: Most days I tend to keep myself busy because I am a full-time student and I work part-time. I am reserved around people I don't know but am very fun and energetic around familiar faces. I can accommodate to situations easily and enjoy switching things up every now and then. Sometimes I feel lonely since I am by myself, but I like being independent and on my own. I like being challenged and taking risks depending on what it is. I am very considerate and think of other before myself. I am kind and love spending time with my family so I try to go home on the weekends as much as I can. I enjoy figuring people out and meeting new people.

name: Maaya George
GenItems_narr:
I usually wake up feeling pretty exhausted, like I want to sleep more. I'm usually a very late sleeper and knock out around 2am on my good days. I feel lethargic and tired most of my day, but when I talk to people and see my friends it gives me energy! I like dressing up cute and going to school, and I like attending my lectures and learning new things. I feel like I find happiness being around people, talking, and laughing. I am a social person when people get to know me, but I can seem shy and reserved at first glance.

I feel really anxious sometimes, and I don't know why. I am super self-conscious about how I look at all times and it can really take a toll on me mentally. I am always thinking about how I am being perceived by people.  I always feel like my head is in the clouds, I am always daydreaming and I think it's because I want to be bigger and better than I currently am. I want motivation to do more with my life, to really shine, but I feel like my anxiety stops me. I desire love and attention, and I want someone to fall in love with me to be completely honest. I desire a boyfriend or girlfriend. I am happy with my academics but I also desire more opportunities to express myself creatively. I wish I had more free time to crochet, learn how to make music, and learn how to make 3D renders but school, work, family, and friends take up most of my time.

name: Sara Lindstrom
GenItems_narr:
I usually feel pretty good about my day. I wake up early most days and I'm always happy to take the bus to campus. I really enjoy looking out of the window and observing the people on the bus or biking around. Then when I get to campus I get tired pretty fast and sometimes I fall asleep in class. I hate when I do that. I feel uncomfortable being alone sometimes, especially when I'm eating. I never eat if I have to eat alone in public. My friend Maaya is with me a lot. We have the same career path so we get to work together a lot on passion projects outside of school. Maaya is a great friend and I'm really grateful for her. But we don't say stuff like that to each other because we aren't really mushy like that. She makes me laugh so hard. I like having classes with her. She gets me out of my shell and I'm less quiet. 

My graphic design class stresses me out a lot. I feel so stupid in that class. I feel like I'm really behind all the time and I can't do anything right. I'm bad with computers. I don't understand things I'm expected to know how to do already because everyone else does. I always leave that class feeling depressed. I have it on Mondays and Wednesdays. I write little "good luck" notes in my planner on those days so I don't dread those days so much. Luckily I sit next to two really nice and helpful girls who I can talk to. My professor intimidates me a lot and I don't feel like I can ask for help.

I think about my boyfriend so much. I feel like he's a big distraction from my academic life. I try to balance it but I'm really weak and I give in and hang out with him when I should do work. I never let it actually affect me academically though. I saw something online about how men make fun of women for being emotional and gossiping but they said that interpersonal relationships are often the biggest factor in determining someone's happiness in their life. That makes me feel better for sometimes prioritizing my boyfriend or my friends and social life over doing the most work possible for my classes.

name: Katie Schwenker
GenItems_narr:
I've recently had more trouble getting up in the morning because I feel unmotivated. I really like my classes but I've been having issues socially. I mostly only talk to a very small group of people: my boyfriend, my best friend, her roommate, and my roommate. I often feel lonely during the day because I feel like I need to branch out and talk to more people.
