GenItems_Unique_item_3: I find that my mood and mental state are determined how others perceive me
GenItems_Unique_item_4: do not like Tuesdays and Thursdays
GenItems_Unique_item_5: I try to be as nice and generous to my first year friend
GenItems_Unique_item_7: I find myself the type of person that matches others' energy
GenItems_Unique_item_9: I may have spread myself a little too thin

name: Aanya Parekh
GenItems_narr:
I am a pretty routine based person and wake up around the same time each day. I wake up and have coffee before going to class. I usually do not have breakfast and have an early lunch and dinner instead. I find that I work better in the mornings and try to have my classes earlier in the day when I can. I try my best to spend a lot of time outside of dorm and will sit in one of the buildings or the benches when the weather is nice and study. . Sometimes I feel "clocked out" by five or six pm but recently it's been better. I do have a late chemistry lab that goes from 7:10 - 10 pm. I find that I have a lot of dread before my labs even though everything turns out fine. I start to get very exhausted near the end of the day I used to have a very hard time falling asleep at night and sometimes I still do. However, I think being busier and not feeling aimless throughout the day, as well as walking, biking and moving around a lot has helped me rest easier. 

I am currently a first year at UC Davis. I have felt really lonely being away from everyone I know. It has gotten better in the winter quarter but still persists. Especially in the first quarter, if I was out the whole day, I would realize I went the whole day without talking to anyone (until I went back and talked with my roommates). Moving has brought a lot of old problems and insecurities, especially with how I feel towards myself and peers. I fear incompetence and part of that includes feeling socially competent but the lack of close relationships hindered that.

name: Madelyne Augustine
GenItems_narr:
My baseline mood tends to be fairly neutral though I consistently experience anxiety throughout the day. My anxiety gets bad anytime I have to plan out anything. So, before I have to go places, I am particularly stressed. My job on the weekends makes me feel exhausted. Im always stretched thin and snap easily at people on the days I work. But I like my coworkers which is my incentive for going most days. I am fairly outgoing and hang out with a lot of different people though I'm typically nervous in social situations. 
I tend to be particularly affected by changes in my schedule that impact my food, exercise, light or sleep. The consistency in my routine helps my anxiety and when it is thrown off for a day, I tend to have a few days following in which my anxiety is heightened. Unfortunately, my schedule is thrown off every weekend when I have work. Overall, I'm usually stressed. I am rather emotionally vulnerable and tend to experience a lot of emotional arousal in response to my perceived failures and social conflict. I have therapy on Thursdays which typically makes me a little more sad the rest of the day. My classes on tuesday make the entire day feel like a chore. I have 5 straight hours of lecture. I usually go home and go to sleep right after because im so mentally drained.

name: Isabella Yoshiyama
GenItems_narr: I consider myself a creature of habit, I love having a routine every day and every day seems quite similar which helps me in terms of organization. Most days I eat the same breakfast. I go to the gym almost every day in the time slot I have been given it. I wouldn't know if I consider myself a morning or a night person. I feel like in the morning my body has energy but my mind doesn't since I like getting exercise or physical chores in the morning but at night I feel like its the other way around, my mind has energy but my body doesn't and this is when I most advance my homework. I consider myself an introvert, I need days to myself to recharge and only have a close group of friends in which I can confide.

name: Valaree Resendes
GenItems_narr:
I am usually very productive in the morning (9am-12pm). I get excited to get things done and feel accomplished. When I go home (because I am a commuter) from UCD I feel drained, especially if there's traffic that day. Even when I am drained, I feel the need to get things done because of the amount of course work and studying I have to do. I also get distracted very easily so it's sometimes difficult to get a lot done in one sitting. 

On the weekends and any breaks I get in between school, I like to thrift and it's probably my favorite hobby. Because of this, I have a small business buying and reselling vintage clothing. Every other week I sell vintage clothing at a market in Davis. Besides thrifting, actually selling at markets is another one of my favorite things to do. It excites me knowing that there are people out there that enjoy the same things I do. Seeing someone excited to buy something that I curated is so fulfilling.
GenItems_Unique_item_8: have to get things done when drained

name: Kylie Luo
GenItems_narr:
I think thank my day-to-day is typically pretty mundane; I have a set schedule per day with very little wiggle room. And honestly, that's how I like it. I've realized that having to constantly work allows me to distract myself from things that trouble me, and that when I have free time, that I think I am at my worst. Every day I eat breakfast at 9:15AM, and from there, go to my classes, labs, sports etc. until around 11PM and then go back and sleep, just to do it again the next day. The system works for me. 

However weekends tend to be a little more difficult to fill as I don't have classes. Usually I go study in the library for a few hours and then spend time with my friends. I typically party on the weekends even though I don't think about myself as a party person. I think it's mostly FOMO. 

I tend to be a pretty quiet person and be very shy around others, however when I get to know people and they get to know me, I start to feel a lot more comfortable and honest. This has always been a little difficult for me because I find it extremely difficult to relate to people, for no particular reason (that I can identify), which makes me feel closed and emotionally unavailable. 

However, sometimes I am content with who I am and the way I am, although it's not often. I feel like I am at constant competition and always need to be better or smarter.

name: Emma Allred
GenItems_narr:
I am currently a student attending Davis and sometimes I think with my education I can be very passive. I try my best during the school but I feel like I have a hard time trying to set goals for myself in the future. I am very much a  person who thinks on things I could do in the present and what can i do now to for myself in the future. I am a more introverted person and I really enjoy finding creative outlets whether that is drawing or watching movies and tv. I say that I enjoy the stuff and when I do i really enjoy creativity, but I also have a hard time finding the time to sit down and do hobbies outside of school. 
     I am generally a happy person but I think at times especially at night, I tend to get anxious and even existential about what could happen in specific situations. Wondering where I will be, how my relationships with my friends are, the future with my partner and other things that could happen if I think hard enough about them.  Throughout my day to day life, I really find pleasure when I have time to walk around and listen to music, being able to listen to music for me is revitalizing. Except this experience is currently being hindered because only one side of my headphones work and I can't find the case to my wireless headphones. I live in an apartment far away from my family. Well they live in California but more south then me. I miss them sometimes and I wonder how my dynamics change since I have moved for college. I especially miss my twin sister. I feel like day to day i try to find little things for self care and finding little ways to enjoy myself. Buying a treat ,listening to music or even looking outside the window in a packed bus on the way to school. When its the weekends I try to find an activity to do whether that getting coffee or roaming around stores.

name: Katelynn Hernandez
GenItems_narr: I’m currently a senior and I am stressed about my classes. I want to pass all of them. It is currently around midterm season so I am studying as much as I can but I know I procrastinate. I live with my boyfriend, we have to be okay with our ups and downs which makes going back to my apartment awkward. Some days it is okay. Mostly everyday I prefer to eat my meals in silence by myself. I believe this is because I grew up eating meals by myself as my family doesn’t eat together. I’ve grown independent as I haven’t lived with them for years but I still come back on weekends which leads to arguments.
GenItems_Unique_item_8: Live with boyfriend leads to awkwardness
GenItems_Unique_item_9: I try studying but I procrastinate

name: Cindy Lam
GenItems_narr:
Most days, I feel excited about doing my daily tasks, but I often feel stressed because of coursework. At times, stress makes it difficult for me to sleep which causes me to feel tired the next evening. 

As a child, I was very extroverted and did not care what other's had to say. After transferring to an academy, I became obsessed with academics. I feel that this negatively impacted my social skills, which I am working to improve upon. Generally, when I'm around peers, I often feel out of place because I am on the quieter side. I feel like I have trouble holding a conversation and always wonder if what I'm saying will offend anyone and if they will accept me. It takes me a longer period of time to become comfortable with people compared to others. Some of my friend's said I looked cold/mean/smart kid at first so it was hard for them to approach me but when they saw me talk to other students and approach them, their negative perceptions changed to positive ones.

I am also a first generation and I often compare myself to my successful older brothers (they're 10 years older than me) because I want to be proud of myself and want my parents to also be proud of their daughter.

name: Rachel Murphy
GenItems_narr: Around people I like or feel comfortable with, I’m outgoing. People say I’m quirky and have an energetic or bubbly personality and they’re kind of right. I actually think I just feel things deeply so I’m just feeling deep excitement and showing it bc I like being around my friends. If I’m not with my friends, I’m generally very quiet. I’m shy, but I like giving out random complement to people who are wearing cute outfits. I like making them happy because it makes me feel like a good person. I act like a know it all because I’d like to think I’m smart but I’m really compensating because I know I’m probably of average intelligence at best. On the subject of feeling deeply, I have shows and movies that I get completely obsessed with and that is all I can think about. I feed the addiction by reading and watching a lot of other people talk about the thing I like. These obsessions can last a while, anywhere between two months to half a year is standard (I think). Because I feel deeply, I get frustrated and annoyed, which means I get snappy with people. I usually regret the things I say (even when I’m not angry) and I dwell on these thoughts frequently. As of late, I’ve been hating biking down the same path, I’d rather walk because I enjoy walking and it’s easier to listen to music that way.

name: Catherine Tate
GenItems_narr:
I typically like to stay busy during the school week, because attending lots of events is fun and it gives me strict times to get schoolwork done. The more time I have available to complete an assignment, the less focused I'll be while working on it, so it takes me the full amount of time. This makes me feeling unproductive, because I know I could have done the assignment in less time plus another activity. On average, I attend three club events a week (meetings or socials). The main clubs I'm involved in are Rotaract, which is a community service club, and American Institute of Chemical Engineers (AIChE). I also attend free events I see advertised on campus, such as puppy therapy during finals, free Mondavi shows, the Aggies Leading the Way Conference, blood drives, etc.

My class schedule this quarter has 8:00AM classes Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays. My last class ends at 7:00PM on Tuesdays and Thursdays. My school days are long because I try and attend all office hours for my classes (professor, TA, and tutor). I spend most of my time on campus, which I think is good for me because I'm more productive when I'm around other people doing work than when I'm alone in my bedroom. My schedule this quarter is one that matches up well with my study habits. 

To keep track of all my classes and events, I have a very detailed Google Calendar. I'll leave a few breaks throughout the day, but mostly I know what I should be doing at any given moment. I also color code activities, so I know at a glance what my day will be like (school heavy, club activities, socializing, chores, etc.).

I don't know what time of day I work best, but I do know that any time after 10PM I don't work well, and it's never been worth it for me to stay up past midnight to do homework, though I'll still try sometimes.
GenItems_Unique_item_6: good time of day to work
GenItems_Unique_item_9: doing what I should be based on Google Calendar
GenItems_Unique_item_10: working well after ten at night

name: Perla Guzman
GenItems_narr: Most days I feel a bit overwhelmed about all the work I need to do, but I do tend to feel excited about going to lecture since they are always interesting. I typically feel happy whenever I run into my friends on campus, but most of the time I am usually by myself so, for the most part of the day, I feel a bit neutral. On Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays, and sometimes Fridays, I don't come back to my apartment until late at night because of either studio classes, film viewings, or club meetings, so I tend to feel extremely exhausted by the time Friday comes.

name: Mahek Bhora
GenItems_narr:
I'm not a morning person so I don't enjoy waking up too early. I like having classes begin at 10 am though because that forces me to wake up by 9am at the latest and get start to my day earl enough for me to feel like I still have the whole day ahead of me. On an ideal day, I'd try to eat breakfast in the morning, do my makeup, hair, and wear nice clothes so I feel ready and excited for the day. I also enjoy sunny weather in comparison to cloudy/cold/grey skies because they just dampen my mood. 

I also like to run into my friends on campus or in the hallways of the place where I live because it is always nice to see familiar faces and catch up. I also like to be productive, but I do have a bad habit of procrastinating on my work and then feeling so useless at the end of the day because of that. I hope I can start reading more and taking walks to have breaks in my day because those sound nice.
GenItems_Unique_item_2: like starting my day at nine am
GenItems_Unique_item_4: get ready and do makeup and wear nice clothes

name: Julie Kim
GenItems_narr:
I am a first-year student and I usually start off my day at either 12 pm or 8 am. Some days I have late classes and I am a heavy sleeper. On other days, I will struggle to wake up for my 9 am class. I rarely eat breakfast and sometimes I skip lunch as well. I wear Invisalign so it is uncomfortable to snack and eat during the day. Because of this, I can be very tired and cranky during the day. On Tuesdays and Thursdays, I will want to take a nap during the day which makes it hard to focus during class. 

I do not own a bike, so I typically walk or take the bus everywhere. On days that I walk, it takes me around 20-30 minutes to get to class because I live off campus. While walking, my feet hurt and I can become very tired and out of breath. This is why I prefer to bus. I love hanging out with my friends whenever I have free time. Being around my friends makes me happy and energetic no matter how tired I am. I'm usually a very positive and loud person but when I have a lot of homework, I become very quiet and sleepy.

name: Jiakang Pei
GenItems_narr: I feel tired on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays because I have 8am courses. Tuesdays and Thursdays are relatively free, I have fewer courses. on Saturdays and Sundays, I feel happy because I can do whatever I want to do.

name: Lauryn Chinn
GenItems_narr: In my daily life, I tend to experience a variety of emotions from happiness to sadness. I reminisce on the past which causes me to feel sadness and I also feel stressed throughout the day due to classes and assignments. I enjoy hanging out with friends or going to the gym which helps me to relieve some of my stress.

name: Jillian Ngo
GenItems_narr:
I am often very calm and mellow most of the day. But sometimes when I am in classes where I sit with new people I met, I sometimes get internally anxious. I often feel like since I am around new people, I need to put up a good front so they have a good impression of me. I also overthink about what I should have conversations about because I have a hard time thinking about how to connect with people (as much as I want to). I enjoy my lunch break because it is my alone time to eat and I get to watch my favorite shows. After lunch, I have a class that I usually get sleepy in but get excited after class because I get to go home and eat food.
My favorite part of the day is my alone time at night. I sit at the dinner table, where I do my work, decompress, and enjoy my hobbies. Often, my roommate comes over and interacts with me which I don't mind but sometimes throws me off because she occasionally has something to vent or confide in. I appreciate that I am a safe space for her but I often feel like I am cannot present myself with the best energy for her when she approaches me during my relaxation time. In other instances, I have dance practices at night time where I interact with people from my club. Whenever I am around them, I feel motivated and energized. Even if I had a lot on my mind that day or am physically tired, I don't think about the troubles when I am at practice. Sometimes right before practices or meetings, I get extremely nervous anticipating the event but when I am there, I don't feel as scared anymore. When I am nervous I think about the possible things that could happen at the event and that I have to ask people for a ride after since I don't have a car and feel bad about it. 
Also, think about your reasons for experiences/behaviors/etc. Is there another reason you get tired after lunch other than the time of day? What about that lab course ruins your mood? Do specific peers trigger your first gen identity more than others? There are no right or wrong answers. The goal is simply to help you think about yourself and everyday experiences as well as what you think drives those. Even though, night time is when I get to relax, it is often when I do my homework as well. So many days I will feel stressed because of the overwhelming amount of things to handle for the week.

name: Farheen Shah
GenItems_narr: My day revolves around my 5 daily prayers. I wake up early morning around 5:30 everyday to read my first prayer, read my 2nd and 3rd prayer at 12:30 and my 4th and 5th prayer at 5:45. These prayers must be performed withing its timeframe which is why I schedule my day around them. I try to keep a balanced schedule but often am unable to do so. The rest of the day I complete my assignments and study for my classes. I have night class 4 days of the week which is very tiring and it becomes hard to go to class. I have an 8 am class 2 days of the week which is usually very tiring, however I enjoy the class.

name: Sruthi Ramesh
GenItems_narr:
I'm usually a pretty energetic individual who enjoys school, but the overwhelming amount of exams and assignments easily stresses me out. I tend to assume I know more than I do, but then I get stressed the day before my exams because I realize my knowledge has been overestimated. To compensate for my stress, I cope with it by watching TV or going on my phone. I have cut down my coping habits a lot, but I still feel the need to cut down those habits and redirect my energy towards a more suited form of studying.

I also really enjoy spending time with my friends, and I tend to enjoy indoor activities with friends more than going out. I love ordering food in and watching movies and having fun at home.
GenItems_Unique_item_7: TV or going on my phone

name: Yiqi Xu
GenItems_narr:
I think I will start with how my day goes, I usually try to sleep in till 10 or 11 each day but my schedule is getting busy so I have to wake up early and go bed late which I kinda hates. For Tuesdays almost my whole day is being occupied by physics classes and lab, but I do enjoy learning a lot by learning stuff that is above my current level. I try my best to understand them and enjoy deeply discussing these problems or thoughts with my professors. I also enjoy striking up philosophical discussion with my friends at random times of a day. And I enjoy joking around my friends with physical and psychological related jokes. 
Regularly, I enjoy listening music the most time of my day to relax or cheer my mood up, it helps to release my anxiety and pressure a lot. Sometimes I feel like I usually get tired and lazy during afternoon and I would get coffee for myself to keep working. At late night I would have a sudden burst of energy and would stay up to do homework. 
Normally I hang around with close friends, I act like an extrovert when I am around people who talks or listen to the topic I like, but when around a crowd of people I don't know I tend to stay quiet and observe people and what they talk about.
GenItems_Unique_item_4: Tuesday occupied by physics and lab
GenItems_Unique_item_5: Enjoy learning stuff above my level
GenItems_Unique_item_11: music release anxiety and help mental health
GenItems_Unique_item_14: introvert around large group of people
GenItems_Unique_item_17: Lead the topics when around close friends

name: emily sun
GenItems_narr: I am a person who is very prone to mood swings. Will be happy for a little thing to jump up and down, but also a little hiccups can seriously affect the mood. All of my friends will tell me sincerely that they really enjoy spending time with me, but I worry about whether I'm negatively affecting them when I'm with them. (Of course I like them too.) I am an international student from China and feel like I have gone from being an extrovert to a bit of an introvert because of this. I love small animals and now I have adopted a kitten myself. I can get a lot of energy from him, especially when I'm under a lot of pressure to study. I'm a pretty smart kid, but don't like to work hard. The stage when I needed to be quiet when I started studying was always painful, so I would always pile everything up to the end. But this sense of pressure created by leaving it to the last minute can bring me a sense of shame and anxiety. But again, studying is also painful. I'm often torn between self-discipline and undiscipline, and most of the results are still undiscipline hahaha

name: Sam Shoemaker
GenItems_narr:
I am usually a very school-focused and prepared person. I can get stressed out from trying to make all my assignments perfect and getting As in all my classes. Despite this, I try to make time to calm down and have fun, such as having time to myself and going out with my friends. I have the most free  time on Mondays, Tuesdays, Saturdays, and Sundays which is usually when I try to catch up on work or destress. My busiest and most stressful days are Wednesday and Thursday as I have lots of classes and a lab on Thursdays. I often am happiest after my day has ended on Tuesdays and Thursdays because I have choir rehearsal which is rejuvenating. 

While classwork can be stressful, it also gives me a sense of accomplishment when I do well in a class. This pushes me to keep doing well and I feel very happy once I have completed a hard task. The downside of this is that if I do not meet my own expectations of what I could do in an assignment or test, I will feel terrible about myself and shutdown.

In terms of abnormalities over these three weeks, I have an internship interview on 2/10 that I am very worried about because I have not had an interview before. I also am stressed about the responsibility that will come with having an internship along with my schoolwork. Additionally, someone that I love might visit me the weekend of 2/25, which will make my much happier.

I also have midterms on February 16, 17, and 27 and a writing assignment due the 22nd, all which will contribute to my stress in preparation.

name: Paige Devencenzi
GenItems_narr:
On the daily, my life starts when I wake up in the morning. Depending on the day, I'll either wake up early or be able to sleep in. But either way, I wake up usually feeling pretty tired already. Almost a little groggy, feeling like I want/need to sleep more but don't have time to or can't fall back asleep. I'm unsure of the reasoning behind this because on average I get 8 hours of sleep which is said to be good for my age. 

Typically in the morning I am very time orientated, I'm always watching the clock and making sure I stay on time with my morning routine so I can get out the door on time for class or for general plans. There are a lot of steps to my morning routine, so I'm usually just occupied with thinking about all the things I need to do (brush teeth, wash face, moisturize, contacts, eyebrows, chapstick, brush hair, perfume, clean piercings, jewelry, clothes, pack bag, refill water, shoes, etc.) By the time I'm finished getting all ready, I'm usually right on time to leave my apartment and drive to school.

The first experience of the day, outside of my apartment, is the cold weather outside and in my car. It's always freezing in my car and I have to set up the heater a certain way to maximize fast heating. Next I will be thinking about what kind of music I'm in the mood for. Music is a big part of my daily life and it influences how I feel a lot. I make sure to put on something I'm interested in listening to at the moment because it's always based on my current mood. 

I drive to school and park at the parking garage. Some days I do experience a little mild anxiety because I get very anxious when it comes to being late to things. There are a lot of factors that I think about on my drive to school that could cause me to be late. Some for example: being stuck behind the train, being stopped at every red light, a possible car crash, slow drivers, and most importantly traffic. Traffic makes me most anxious because it's sometimes unpredictable but I make sure to allocate enough time in the morning to either beat or accomadate for the traffic. Then I need to think about finding a parking spot which occupies my mind for the next 5-10 minutes as I drive up and through the parking garage. 

Once I've found a spot to park, there are a few things I always make sure I remember. 1. pay for parking, 2. think about what time I should leave my car in order to get to my class at a good time, 3. what music should I play while I walk over there, 4. do I feel like using my airpods or headphones, and 5. remember exactly where you parked and what staircase you took because I have a fear of forgetting my spot and never finding my car again. 

Each day while I'm walking to class, I'll think about random things that I have going on in the day, but mainly I'm listening to my music and singing it in my head. I'm also hyper aware of my walking and I think about it and how people may perceive me based on how I'm walking. 

Every Monday, Tuesday, and Thursday, my first class tires me out really fast. But after those lectures are done, I get coffee which I really look forward to because I love coffee. I also get food during this time for lunch. I'm usually with my friend(s) after my first class too so I'm mainly focused on whatever conversation we're having, thinking about random things.

My other classes for the days really drain me. I have two back to back lectures and usually I'm falling asleep during them because I get super tired. I don't know the reason for this because I make sure to eat food and drink coffee. I think I'm a person who needs little naps throughout the day but that doesn't exactly fit in my everyday schedule. So I just try my best to stay awake and pay attention by taking notes. 

By the end of the day, I usually just think about how tired and hungry I am and how much I want to lay in my bed. While I drive home in the late afternoon, I'm also thinking about what homework and other important tasks I need to do. I also think about upcoming events and what I'm going to get/make for dinner. I enjoy hanging out with my friends on the daily. But some days when I'm really drained, I don't talk much with my housemates because I don't have the energy after a long day. But other days I do look forward to hanging out with them, it really just depends on my mood.

name: Lauryn Chinn
GenItems_narr: In my daily life, I tend to feel a variety of emotions from happiness to sadness. I feel stressed sometimes and may get anxiety attacks which decreases my physical and mental health but I find ways to relieve these stress factors. I enjoy working out at the gym and hanging out with friends in my free time. I also like to play sports, especially basketball, read romantic books or watch movies or tv series. Aside from my hobbies, I am an indecisive and emotional person. I tend to feel empathy for others and I enjoy listening and giving advice to my friends during tough times. It makes me feel happy when I help someone which is also why I want to do something in the medical field because the joy I get from helping people is unmatched.

name: Sydney Wooden
GenItems_narr:
In the mornings I tend to start out tired due to having early classes, but that's also because I tend to go to bed late. I try to make my bed every morning, and it feels off when I can't do it for fear of being late to class. I often skip breakfast due to waking up late, and after my morning class I go to work. Work is peaceful because it allows me to unwind from school work, especially since my supervisor lets us listen to music. I go back to campus for more classes, and then go back to work. The bike rides around school and to work can either be stressful or relaxing depending on how much time I have, the amount of people around, or the weather.

I try to work out most days by going on runs, and I always feel more energetic and in a better mood after. When I'm in a really bad mood, running always helps me get out of my funk. Once home for the evening, I tend to be more happy as I get to catch up with my roommates. It's easier for me to open up to them because I feel more comfortable around them compared to peers in class. When I'm around peers, I tend to feel stressed because I'm worried I'm not as smart or that I don't deserve to be here. I think this is due to a series of bad chemistry grades, which lowered my confidence as a student severely. I also feel like I don't know how to connect with them very well, so I tend to stay quiet, and when no one inevitably talks to me, it fuels my anxiety that I'm not someone people would want to hang around. Dinner is one of my favorite meals because I get distracted from school work, and its a nice way to relax.
 
Before I go to bed, I go on my phone or read or talk to my roommate because I don't like falling asleep without being distracted. If left alone with my own thoughts, I'll eventually stress myself out by contemplating things that are out of my control (state of the world, death, faith, etc. As part of my routine, I'll remove an extra pillow and stuffed animal from my bed so that they're not in the way. 

On Fridays I wake up stressed because I have an early morning class, then only a ten minute gap before my chem lab, which always makes me panic that I'm going to be late even though my ta told me it's okay if I'm a few minutes late. Our first lab also went late and was almost a failure, so I'm always worried that the lab will be really difficult or time consuming, and that I'll somehow mess up and get a bad grade. Afterwards, I go to one of my favorite classes, which always fills me with relief, so Fridays start off bad but end well.

name: Kara Long
GenItems_narr:
To put it bluntly, I have a constant underlying depression that makes everything I do tiring and it is hard to fully enjoy anything I do.
I usually feel most comfortable when I am with my girlfriend, and I get to see her most days.
I am extremely stressed and overwhelmed with classes and writing a thesis so I have been very high-strung and irritable, and sometimes I feel like my behaviors/reactions are more motivated by feelings than rational thoughts, but I am trying to start meditating to improve that.
I tend to have obsessive self-deprecating thoughts, but I usually correct them by telling myself the opposite of whatever I thought, but that too gets tiring and I feel burnt out most of the time. 
I am most energetic in the late morning and start to crash in the late afternoon, likely because I wake up at 4 am to go to the gym.
I run the club People for the Elimination of Animal Cruelty through Education, and every day I spend a bit of time doing some sort of animal rights activity (meetings, emailing to my club, social media posting, etc). Doing things for animal rights is usually enjoyable and energizing, as that is a great passion of mine, but sometimes it gets hard to balance with school and work.
In the mornings, I usually feel like I do not want to go to work (I am a writing tutor) but once I get to work I feel better because I really like my job, as helping others brings me joy and makes me feel useful.
I always dread Tuesdays because I have work, classes, and meetings non-stop from 9 am-6 pm, including my lab for 'Statistical Analysis of Psychological Data'. I absolutely hate that lab because coding is very difficult and confusing for me and I do not like to feel like I am bad at things. I put a lot of pressure on myself to exceed expectations and as much as that stresses me out, I know that over-working myself is a coping mechanism.
I always look forward to Fridays because I do not have classes or work and I get to see an EMDR therapist to hopefully start decreasing the flashbacks and obsessive thoughts I get every day.
My favorite part of the day is going to bed and I look forward to spending calm time at home with my roommate and cat.
I am also looking into potential grad schools and gap year options because I just got denied from the grad school I applied to, so that is a massive weight on my shoulders. However, I am getting some support from the graduate students in the psychology research lab I work in and I like going into the lab and spending time with them.
GenItems_Unique_item_12: animal rights is enjoyable and energizing

name: Emalina Stepanian
GenItems_narr: I start off my days early despite the fact I sleep late, so I'm usually tired when I open my eyes but I get used to the sunlight quickly. I like to give myself 20 minutes in bed after my alarm goes off before I get up to brush my teeth, and wash my face. If I'm staying at home for the morning or the day, I will make my bed and walk outside to the kitchen where I usually greet my best friend and roommate, Emily. We make a quick coffee or breakfast if time allows. Then I head back to my room to either do some studying/homework or get ready for a class. If I need to study I like to do it early in the morning when I feel the most energized because I feel like once the sun sets I get lazier and push off my work, and then I fall behind. I love spending time with my roommate, we cook together, laugh together, do homework together, and we even fly back home for holidays together. This is a good environment I live in for sure. As for my workload, I have a pretty medium-level workload this quarter. The days I despise are Mondays and  Thursdays. I have 2 and half hour physics labs on those days. The reason I don't like physics labs is that I am not too strong when it comes to the subject of physics and the time these lobs take up, also takes a lot of energy from me. I am usually exhausted after lab and can't finish much work. I also talk to my parents from back home on a daily basis. I live 6 hours away and having a strong relationship with them is important to me.

name: Agnes Lee
GenItems_narr:
I am usually optimistic because my motto is every setback is a setup from God so I try to look at bad situations as educational or as self discovery. For example, when I got a flat tire the day before driving down to L.A, I thought," If this didn't happen today, it would've happened on the drive down which would be much more dangerous."  Despite the hassle of finding new tires and the incident completely ruining my schedule and day, I decided to look at it positively. I however have a bad habit of over thinking and making up nonsensical daydreams of what might happen. I am trying to fix that which is quite hard. When I overthink, my stomach turns upside down and I lose my appetite and feel nauseous. 

I am working 2 jobs which I don't mind all too much. I recently started a gymnastics coaching job that is quite fun. From this job, I am learning to stand up for myself because there is a coworker who comes off rude and scolding towards me. This is something I would like to fix about myself. I am also learning this at my house because there is someone who disrespects me.

I am quite forgiving and naïve, so I would like to learn to how to be more quick witted and learn to stand up for myself more.

name: Danny Kuei
GenItems_narr:
I tend to sleep late and wake up right before my first class whether its an early or late class so I usually start the day very tired. Nonetheless, I try my best to focus during lectures. Later on, I do get more energetic and enjoy my daily life as I hangout with my friends on campus or have small talk with strangers. Although its a little weird, I also find myself to be observative as I find interest in looking at random people or eavesdropping in conversations. I find a lot of my classes slow, so I end up multitasking listening to lecture and doing work on my laptop.

Overall I have a pretty busy course load but I find myself motivated when I'm on campus. Even on Tuesdays and Thursdays where I have labs and a full day of class, I still find it fun even if I'm really drained. On weekdays, I come back to my apartment at night and find joy in cooking as I like making new dishes, sometimes with the recipes from my mom. Afterwards I'm on my laptop where I talk and play video games with my friends on discord and/or do school work. Due to my abnormal sleep schedule I get really tired and will pass out on my chair or on my desk a lot of time for around 30 minutes to an hour almost everyday. My daily life is typically uneventful but on weekends I sometimes go to my friends' apartments or go out to downtown. Even on weekends where I stay in all the time, I feel somewhat regretful but am overall alright with it.

name: Yousra Jatt
GenItems_narr:
I am an introvert, and frankly, I would say socially awkward, unfortunately. I wish I wasn't. But I think it stems from how I grew up. My parents were immigrants to the country and socializing for them was difficult, so I think it passed on to me and my siblings since we only socially interacted with a few people. Growing up I didn't see it as an issue but now it is something that I think about almost every day. I think I am mature in the sense that I understand a higher number of friends doesn't mean those friendships are of higher quality, but I do wish I had 1-3 friends that I could count on. So in that sense, I do feel lonely. I think it also doesn't help that as I am getting older, my parents talk about my getting married yet at the same time my mother says you don't have any friends, who will attend your wedding. Perhaps these kinds of comments make me more socially conscious lol.

In fact, I think my social anxiety is so bad that I become very anxious when it comes to presentations and speaking in front of audiences, even if it means answering questions in class. I have been trying to push myself to speak up in class and at least answer the questions I know the answer to for sure that my professors ask. But, for instance, I am supposed to give a presentation for my capstone project as a part of my degree and it makes me very worried. 

I think I am a patient and hardworking person. However, I do get tired easily. I was severely anemic, got treated for it, and it helped. But lately, I am starting to feel low on energy again. This becomes difficult for me as I am in the last semester of my master's program.

I try, and in fact, like to start my mornings early. I feel like I am more productive that way. But this becomes a problem for me when I sleep late. I try to sleep on time, but I live with my family and they're not used to it so it is often very difficult. The same goes for diet. I try to eat healthily but my family is picky. This brings me to my other point, that I moved back in with my family, and I feel like my real personality and behaviors are hidden now and rather restricted. Like I have to follow their rules and timeline, which deviates from who I want to be.

name: Yadira Delgado Diaz
GenItems_narr: When it comes to my day to day experiences is that I tend to fall asleep really early, as I like to get up to go to the gym by the morning or if classes interrupt that then I go earlier than my classes. After the workout session which usually last an hour I am tired and am more calm throughout the day. I am mostly excited to get over my classes due to some not capturing my attention. I believe me getting tired could be me waking up early along with me sleeping for an excessive amount of time which leads to a lot of tiredness. When it comes to a majority of my classes I have confusion as I don't really understand terms and it is more difficult for me to grasp new ideas. When I see others being able to complete such things it makes me wonder if I am behind then I get anxious at the idea that I am not able to do much. Throughout the day I usually complete my class work as a majority of my classes are online this quarter which is to my relief as I don't have to interact with others much. I get a lot of anxiety when interacting with others, it's been like that since I was a kid, for now I don't know why I get such sensations but it happens.

name: Mariah Segura
GenItems_narr:
A little bit about myself is that I'm currently a first year college student. I'm 18 years old and I'm from a small town near Santa Cruz California. I'm currently a human development major and in hopes of pursuing a pathway in the medical field. Everyday I have a constant fear in the back of my head that if I don't succeed in one class, one test, it'll lead to the fear of not succeeding in my ultimate goal. Days that I have mid-terms are very difficult for me because I've never been the best at taking tests. 
On Mondays I start my day off pretty well because my class doesn't start until 12:30. I then therefore am able to either sleep in or go to the gym. I tend to be very eventful on this day because I have a lot of time in between to go to my next class at 6:10pm. Mondays and Wednesdays are the same schedule so they both tend to be the most beneficial days while  getting homework done. Tuesdays I have 3 classes so I tend to be more tired and less energetic. Thursdays tend to be one of the better days of the week. Thursdays have weirdly always been my favorite days of the week because the next day is Friday. On Fridays I don't have class so I have a lot of free time which is one of the reasons why I try to get ahead on homework. 
On a deeper note, I'm a second generation college student. Both of my parents graduated and attended college. Something that makes me self conscious is that both parents are successful especially my mother. Thats interesting to write but because my mother is very successful and it's very hard to tell her when I feel that I'm failing at something.
GenItems_Unique_item_19: I've never been the best at taking test
GenItems_Unique_item_20: Both of my parents attended college

name: Emery Nguyen
GenItems_narr:
Most days I stay home and watch my shows and play videogames. I rarely interact with people as they tire me out. I want a genuine connection with people rather than just a shallow one discussing what music they like. These days I feel that a lot of people are not genuine and just putting on an act to appeal to others.

I often feel stressed thinking about my future. I don't know what the future holds and that scares me. I don't know if I'll succeed despite many saying I will succeed. I still worry despite knowing there are some things out of my control.

name: Shanya Prasad
GenItems_narr:
My daily life in college has been quite interesting. During winter quarter, everyday I woke up around 6-7 am to attend my morning classes. Even though I dread and hate waking up in the morning, I rather stay up at night, I do enjoy starting my day early. Most of my classes end before 1 so I spend most of my after noons doing assignments which makes feel happy and productive. However on Tuesday are my favourite days because I only have one class and it ends at 9:50, which gives me the whole day to catch up on my assignments and relaxing. After class if Im not working on assignments, I'm hanging out with my friends. We are either going out to eat, doing chores, or relaxing. 

In my day to day life I enjoy studying alone, but I also love studying in groups or pairs. Studying with other provides me comfort and give me opportunities to ask questions when I don't understand the homework. Besides the work aspect in my life I love taking naps especially after eating lunch. I often get tired after eating no matter if the food is healthy or not. In addition to getting tired after lunch, sometimes I get tired after to driving back and forth from school and home. Usually throughout a normal day my basic emotions range from being tired, happy, stressed, and relaxed.

name: Stella Truong
GenItems_narr:
During my adolescence, I have changed a lot in my personality. I used to be a social butterfly but now I am quite introverted. On daily basic, I do not communicate much with people around. But, I am happy everyday with my life. On daily basics, I go to classes and to the gym. I have online paper work job. 
My parents do not push a lot pressure of success on me so I am luckily living in the way I wish. I am able to pursue my majors, my projects and my dream. Overall, I am really happy now

name: Elizabeth Churchill
GenItems_narr:
Every day I have track practice so a lot of my thoughts are athletic related, especially because we are in our competition season right now. When I am not exercising I am usually studying. I usually have the same amount of energy throughout the whole day. In the morning maybe a little less. Most of my days are the exact same so I usually only get excited if I am going out with a friend at night. Usually on Fridays my mood is a lot better because I go out with friends and do something fun. When I am around my friends I put on a very friendly face and act very outgoing and social, but in classes I am quiet and keep to myself. 

I have night classes on Monday and Tuesday which I don't look forward to because they are from 6-8pm and I get tired. I have 8am classes on Mon/Wed that I am always up and ready for. I like to start my days early when possible because it makes me feel more productive. I spend most of my time with one of my friends, we do everything together including track. My mood is always better around her as well.
